title: Independent candidate Murtaza Khan wins PK-53 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Murtaza Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-53 Swabi-V by securing 40,825 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party’s Muhammad Zahid who bagged 20,661 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 37.02 per cent.
